subSubSection.paragraph:
Derivatio nominis
: The new species is dedicated to members of the Halada family (Hamr near Chlum u Třeboně, 
Czech Republic
). Jiři Halada, the senior, and his sons Marek and Michal collected – sometimes together with other Czech partners – extensive material of 

Hylaeus

from numerous African countries and provided much of their collection to the Biology Centre of the Oberösterreichisches Landesmuseum, Linz (
Austria
). The material was collected with expertise, the specimens are excellently prepared – it is a joy to work with.
